{Burnt Mill Farm}has been owned and farmed by the Ward family for 30 years. They breed cows on the farm and there are about 100 in all. The calves are sold after a year. Mr Ward owns about 30 acres of grassland. He thinks the farm is too small to warrant use of computers.
{Park Farm}is called this because of the University Parks nearby. The farm buildings were built in about 1900. It is a livestock farm with 100 acres of grassland. They use modern machines but not computers for the paperwork. They sell the calves at the market in Banbury.
There are 4 other farms in Marston, {Cannons Farm, Hill Farm, Colthorns} {Farm}and{Cherwell Farm.}
